 includes contributions by both English and Russian scholarsMansfield’s personal and artistic response to Russian literature, culture, philosophy, and artExplores her responses to the actual Russians she met in England and — towards the end of her life — in France  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 4aLiterary Studies. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / Eastern (see also Russian & Former Soviet Union).2bisacsh1 aAdcock, Fleur, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aButler, Pierce, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDavison, Claire, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDiment, Galya, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKimber, Gerri, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aKimber, Gerri, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLipsey, Roger, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarshall, Owen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMartin, W. Todd, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aNadel, Ira, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRampton, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReading, Frances, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWhiteley, Giles, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWhyte, Jessica, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZimring, Rishona, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311078140340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781474426152?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www